Author: University of Minnesota PreCalculus Dept.
Reviewed/Remixed by: Doenet team

About the problem: Given a quadratic equation, determine the constant k required to form a perfect square. A graphing tool is provided for checking solutions graphically.

The Worked Example can be hidden by commenting out the <hint> portion of the document.

*************************************************************-->

<problem><title/>
<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="e" from="1" to="100" exclude="1 4 9 16 25 36 49 64 81"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="d" from="-20" to="20" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="p" from="-4" to="4" exclude="0"/>
  <math name="k" simplify>$p $e</math>
  <math name="a" simplify>-$k / $e</math>
  <math name="exprVertexForm">$a (x - $d)^2 + $k</math>
  <math name="expr" expand simplify="numberspreserveorder">$exprVertexForm</math>
  <math name="sol1">$d + sqrt($e)</math>
  <math name="sol2">$d - sqrt($e)</math>
</setup>


<!--testing-->
<!-- <p>a = $a</p>
<p>d = $d</p>
<p>e = $e</p>
<p>p = $p</p>
<p>k = $k</p>
<p>exprVertexForm = $exprVertexForm</p>
<p>expr = $expr</p>
<p>sol1 = $sol1</p>
<p>sol2 = $sol2</p> -->
<!--testing-->

<p>Solve the following equation by completing the square. Your final answer will have two solutions of the form <m>x = a \pm \sqrt{b}</m>.</p>


<p><me>$expr = 0</me></p>


<!--*********************************************
            Graphing Tool
**********************************************-->

<aside><title>Graphing tool</title>

<setup>
  <number name="xmin">min($d - 20, $d - sqrt($e)-20)</number>
  <number name="xmax">max($d + 20, $d + sqrt($e)+20)</number>
  <number name="ymin">min($k - 20, -20)</number>
  <number name="ymax">max($k + 20, 20)</number>
</setup>
  
<sideBySide margins="5%" widths="30% 70%">
<div><p>Graph parabola with given equation:</p> 
  <p><m>y = </m> <mathInput name="eq1"/></p>

  <p>Graph proposed solutions:</p> 
  <p><m>x = </m><mathInput name="x1" bindValueTo="$userSol1"/></p>
  <p><nbsp/><nbsp/><nbsp/><nbsp/>or</p>
  <p><m>x = </m> <mathInput name="x2" bindValueTo="$userSol2"/></p>
  <p>Which yields roots of $r1, $r2.</p>
</div>
  
<graph name="g1" xmin="$xmin{link='false'}" xmax="$xmax{link='false'}" ymin="$ymin{link='false'}" ymax="$ymax{link='false'}">
  <function name="givenParabola">$eq1</function>
  <point name="r1" fixed styleNumber="5">($x1, 0)</point>
  <point name="r2" fixed styleNumber="5">($x2, 0)</point>
</graph>
  
</sideBySide>

<p>If your solutions are correct the graphed roots will occur at the intersection points of the given parabola with the <m>x-</m>axis.</p>

</aside>  


  
<p>Solutions: <m>x = </m> <mathInput name="userSol1"/> or 
<m>x = </m> <mathInput name="userSol2"/></p>

  <answer name="ans1">
    <award name="allCorrect" unorderedCompare>
      <when>($userSol1, $userSol2) = ($sol1, $sol2)</when>
    </award>
  </answer>



